1.title: Mystery Trailer
1.plot: Sean tows a mysterious trailer to the auction and everyone wonders what's inside. T Money and Papa Bear battle over bins while Brandon and Lori play different kinds of games.

2.title: Dying to Know
2.plot: The bidders go head to head on a bin full of motorcycle parts.

3.title: Bid 'Em Up
3.plot: An item in one bin has Papa Bear and Mone revving their engines, while T Money gambles on guns being hidden in another bin.

4.title: Rolling Thunder
4.plot: A bin from "down under" holds a dark and mysterious surprise.

5.title: Too Hot!
5.plot: In the sweltering heat, the bidders must fight for the ultimate blind buy - a unit completely hidden behind a sheet of plastic!

6.title: His Way
6.plot: Brandon arrives solo to the auction but still flexes his muscle.

7.title: Dropping Anchor
7.plot: Jessie hopes to find some hidden gems in a bin full of old furniture.

8.title: The Big One
8.plot: The bidders take a trip to Canyon Country to bid on huge trailers. A mysterious concrete block and a trailer full of hay mean big opportunities and lead to unusual alliances within the group.

9.title: Brandon vs. Lori
9.plot: Lori and Brandon get in a fight over a bin and make a wager to see who can do better. Lori eyes a bin with a tanning bed, while a bin with fake walls intrigues Brandon.

10.title: After Dark
10.plot: When Sean is only allowed in the storage facility after hours, it results in the first ever day to night auction, ending in the dark!

11.title: All's Fair
11.plot: Sean takes the bidders to the home of the L.A. County Fair for a behind the scenes tour.

12.title: Underwater in Hawaii
12.plot: The bidders take a trip out to Hawaii for an auction at a marine life park.

13.title: Flying High

1.title: Bloody Battle
1.plot: Husband and wife team, Brandon and Lori Bernier, travel the United States in search of rare treasures at various storage facility auctions.

2.title: Cash Wars
2.plot: Brandon and Lori go to war over a record producer's storage unit and unearth what could be a priceless piece of rock and roll history. Then, Jesse one ups the competition for a locker with a multi-thousand dollar payout. And, a booby-trapped unit explodes, sending shock-waves through the storage facility.

3.title: Brawlin' on the Bayou
3.plot: Brandon and Lori look to cash in on their first big trip to New Orleans, but they'll have to fight the locals off. Then, the Taylor Brothers wage war to win a locker loaded with hunting and sporting equipment. And, fireworks explode when a locker full of liquor and rare Mardi Gras masks spark a crazy war.

4.title: Rednecks & Riches
4.plot: Brandon And Lori are back at the bayou and they are ready to get their hands and cash on the right abandoned lockers. Local legend FJ sees big dollar signs in old voodoo artifacts. Brandon and Lori unearth a rare find with a potentially priceless payout. And all bets are off when a bidding war over endangered species taxidermy ends in a heated stand-off with the local authorities.

5.title: Gamblin' Gods
5.plot: The buyers press their luck in Sin City where Brandon and Lori get outfoxed by a group of locals with a questionable strategy. Then, Jesse gambles on a locker filled with junk. Everyone thinks he's crazy, but he knows something they don't. And, vintage slot machines and poker tables send bidding through the roof. The closing price is stratospheric, but what's hidden from sight will be the ultimate payday one lucky bidder.

6.title: Disaster Strikes!
6.plot: Jesse taunts Brandon and Lori in the hopes of instigating a fight and later unearths a ticking treasure. Then, seasoned local Victor throws down his bankroll for a trove of luxury goods, but are they actually knock-offs? And, Brandon and Lori think they've hit the jackpot with a cache of firearms, but when Lori's gun accidentally goes off inside the locker, Brandon is caught in the cross-hairs.

7.title: Boston Bad Blood
7.plot: Brandon and Lori return to Boston and square off against his former protégé Wade. The bad blood may just erupt into a full-out brawl on the auction floor. Then, a former military hero goes all in on a locker that turns out to be hiding the ultimate score. And, the contents of a unit spark an outrage among the buyers, but Brandon only sees dollar signs. Will he walk away or will this controversial cache crush his morals?

8.title: Score of the Century
8.plot: The score of a lifetime is hidden in the back of what already appears to be a great locker, but when the bidding heats up, will our auction heroes have the cash to stay in this game? But first, Brandon and Lori face a shocking discovery when the contents of what look like an old retail store reveal their true identity. And, some rare antiques fetch a fair price but further exploration of a hidden whale tusk could mean a windfall for one lucky storage hunter.

9.title: Old Rivals, New Wars
9.plot: When the Taylor brothers show up, Brandon and Lori have a new civil war on their hands. An accident in a winning bin brings out the fire fighters and another kind of heat for Brandon and Lori. With the southern boys snatching up bins left and right, Brandon and Lori have no choice but to team up with a long time rival. But will they score big or bust?

10.title: Cash Dash
10.plot: A smelly bin scares away most bidders, but it ends up being a great score for T-Money. Brandon and Lori win a scary bin that may or may not have value. Brandon and Lori believe the Taylor brothers sabotaged their plans and it comes down to blows for the boys. You don't mess with Brandon and Lori's business!

11.title: Medieval Melee
11.plot: Buyers haggle over a locker filled with vintage surfing gear; Brandon and Lori get a busted bin that contains a glass case filled with an unidentifiable goo. Later, things get overly intense during the day's final auction.

12.title: Dirty Deeds, Dirtier Dealings
12.plot: The buyers try their luck with vault units in sunny San Diego. Brandon and Lori try to stick the Taylor brothers with a questionable vault but it may just end biting them in the rear. Terrell hits it big with a vault everyone thought was worthless and the Taylor brothers win a vault with a wet-bike.

13.title: Dirty Gold Rush
13.plot: Our buyers lock horns to win a unit packed with valuable construction equipment. Then, Brandon and Lori spot something that no one else does, but they'll have to play it cool if they want to walk away with this golden score.

14.title: Native Wars
14.plot:
Know what this is about?
 Be the first one to add a plot.

15.title: Smoking Hot
15.plot: Minds are blown when two of our buyers team up for a major score. It's an unlikely pair that, together, could make a pile of cash. Plus, Jesse takes a big gamble on some African art and sweats it out hard when the authenticity is questioned. And later, the day's final auction reveals contents so shocking our buyers may be shut out of this game completely.

16.title: Triple X
16.plot: Our buyers bid big to win a locker packed with what looks like rare art, but will the winner walk away with cash or counterfeits?

17.title: Built for Speed
17.plot: Our buyers go head-to-head to score an item that appears to be a covered car. But when the tarp is pulled back, will the winner drive away with a pile of cash or a piece of trash?

18.title: Buyer Beware
18.plot: A covered car lures our buyers to bid big, but the reveal could be more than the winner bargained for. Then, as the temperature climbs to the hottest day of the year, Jesse loses out to Dan on a locker full of expensive tools.

19.title: Fishing for Trouble
19.plot: The competition is off with a bang as a locker full of fishing gear sparks fast and furious bidding war that leaves the winner with a surprise catch.

20.title: All Out War
20.plot: Our buyers throw down to win a locker packed with recreational equipment and what looks like a hidden tractor. But when the dust settles and the cover's pulled back, one lucky hunter gets the surprise of a lifetime. Then, after a period of probation, the Taylor brothers return to stake their claim and they've brought a pile of cash. And later, after being outbid on every unit, one of our buyers loses his mind in a do-or-die bidding war that drives the price through the roof. It's a risky proposition that could make or break the winning bidder's bankroll.

21.title: Judgment Day
21.plot: Our buyers are in for the fight of their lives as they lock horns at the nation's biggest shipping container auction.

1.title: Bid or Die
1.plot: Newbies Scott and Chrissy push their way onto Brandon and Lori's turf forcing the couple to burn cash like never before. Then, a set of wrapped pallets heats up the competition.

2.title: Never a Safe Bet
2.plot: Arch-enemies drop their guard to team up against a new threat.? Then, it's back to the future when Desert Dan risks all on a tire and a hunch.?

3.title: Checkmate
3.plot: Jesse knows you don't strike it rich if you play it safe, so he gambles big on a risky bin.

4.title: Double Cross
4.plot: Big money brings out fierce competition at a rare high-stakes RV auction. Then, the contents of a locker spill out at our bidders' feet, smashing several dangerous objects.

5.title: Once in a Lifetime
5.plot: A deadly bin puts all the buyers on edge. It's a bad omen that casts a dark shadow over the day. As the day winds to a fever pitch, Brandon and Lori square off against Scott and Chrissy in a do or die bidding war that sends all strategy out the window.

6.title: Naughty Hands & Crazy Pants
6.plot: Cash flies over a locker that reveals a high-ticket mystery item. Then, everyone digs deep to win an ATM, but when the dust settles will this thing be filled with big bucks or major regret?

7.title: Bowling for Billions
7.plot: In Vegas, an old rivalry resurfaces. Then, a locker reveals a covered item that's thought to be a vintage car, but when the bidding ends will the buyer drive away with a fortune or stall out in failure?

8.title: Sin City Sucker Punch
8.plot: A mega-find leaves the winning bidder scratching his head, but when the true nature of this item is revealed he'll be swimming in more than just cash.

9.title: Now You See It, Now You Don't
9.plot: Mystery is the name of the game as Brandon and Lori uncover a vintage machine filled with risqu? photos. It's tantalizing, but is it profitable? Then, our buyers lock horns in a bidding war over what could be priceless artwork.

10.title: This Can't Be!
10.plot: Brandon and Lori take a risk on a large covered item during an unusual auction. Will the reveal rev their profits or stall their cash flow?

11.title: Swollen Profits
11.plot: Buyers get stung when a locker unleashes a swarm of more than just merchandise. Then, when our buyers back away from a bin piled sky high with rusty office cabinets one hawk-eyed competitor sees something no one else does.

12.title: Business in a Box
12.plot: The buyers come face-to-face with one of the strangest lockers ever seen. It's an odd opportunity that sends the bidding through the roof, but when the door is unlocked, Pandora's box reveals a surprise that sends its winning bidder through the roof.

13.title: Hold Tight & Bid High
13.plot: Cash is falling from the sky as our buyers go head to head at the biggest airport auction ever seen. Jesse gambles hard on a mystery box with a telling message.

14.title: Men at War
14.plot: Our buyers throw down to win a locker packed with recreational equipment and what looks like a hidden tractor. But when the dust settles and the cover's pulled back, one lucky hunter gets the surprise of a lifetime.

15.title: Stormy Waters
15.plot: With Sean as the captain, the biggest of the big-time bidders head to Marina Del Rey in search of true nautical treasures.

16.title: Claws for Cash
16.plot: Scott shoots the moon on a bin that may cost him an arm and a leg. Then, T-Money spies a prize that could send him straight to the top. Plus, Brandon and Jesse lock horns in a do or die bidding war that could send one of them to the retirement home. And later, the claws come out when the tension between Lori and Chrissy boils over.

17.title: Truth or Dare
17.plot: T Money puts his honesty to the test with shocking revelations.

18.title: Torching the Competition
18.plot: Things get hairy for the hunters as some ring in the money while others go for broke.

19.title: Fuel to the Fire
19.plot: In a day filled with explosive surprises, Team Brandori looks for a big win as the Alvarado Brothers take a gamble and let the pros get under their skin.

20.title: Dangerous Methods
20.plot: Brandon and Lori go for the gold - but find something even better.

21.title: Mother Truckers
21.plot: In one of the most unusual big money auctions yet, Sean auctions the contents of abandoned big-rigs. Scott and Jesse go head to head over a space age haul, while Brandon and Lori take a chance on a battle-ready rig. Meanwhile, Papa Bear goes all in for some vintage fun stuff - and he isn't in the mood to play games.

22.title: Rhinestones and Thrones
22.plot: It's wheels up for Papa Bear when he takes a gamble on a mysterious covered item. Meanwhile, the newcomer Alvarado brothers find an unusual collectible hiding in plain sight -- but are they going to flush their money down the toilet? And Brandon and Lori find out whether a pet bin will turn out to be their best friend.?

23.title: Bear Hunters
23.plot: Does Big Bear mean Big Money? The Alvarados get sneaky while Desert Dan horses around, and frustration gets the best of Brandori. Do they strike gold or strike out? As Jesse crushes dreams, who will go home empty-handed??

24.title: Risky Business
24.plot: Brandon goes out on a limb, and finds himself sinking in quicksand with no help from Lori - will Desert Dan lend him a hand? Dan's car smarts come in handy, while T Money rocks out with his win.

25.title: Going for Broke
25.plot: Scott blows his wad on an Oktoberfest bin, and will have to drown his sorrows. The Alvarado Brothers bid big on collectibles -- will they draw a wild card? T-Money rides away with a big win, while Brandon and Lori investigate a crime scene bin.

26.title: Deceptive Deals
26.plot: Scott and Chrissy's last hurrah. Brandon and Lori win the big prize, but it turns out all that glitters is not gold.

1.title: Buried Alive
1.plot: Moné, Brandon and Lori's new nemesis, arrives on the scene.

2.title: Behind Closed Doors
2.plot: This is an unusual auction with two huge specialty items.

3.title: Lock and Load
3.plot: T-Money wins a mysterious bin with a massive, chained up steel door.

4.title: Bling & Bang
4.plot: The big tension of the day is between T-Money and Brandon. T goes for the mystery bins - the box and the barrels.

5.title: Winter Wonderland
5.plot: A trip to Lake Arrowhead brings rain, snow and a new couple who drive Brandori crazy.

6.title: Out with the Old
6.plot: The new couple (aka: the "younger, trendier Brandon and Lori") are back.

7.title: The Dancing Bear
7.plot: Papa Bear is back, and he's bigger than ever. He goes for a pair of mysterious blue shipping cases. Brandon and Lori find a 3D printer, but have no idea what it does or how much it's worth until they take it to get appraised. What they find out amazes them.

8.title: Surfs Up in Canyon Country
8.plot: Jesse and Papa Bear team up to go after a barbed-wire-protected safe. It's a big day for Brandon and Lori - they score an awesome sand rail and a vintage surfboard, which turns out to be highly collectible.

9.title: Sound the Alarm
9.plot: Papa Bear sees a clue in a bin that leads him to believe there's a shotgun hidden in it. Lori teams up with Jesse behind Brandon's back to win the big specialty item at the end of the day.

10.title: The Art of the Bid
10.plot: Lori knows from her research that two of these bins previously belonged to the same owner. She and Brandon win one of them, an aviation bin; now they have to find the other one.

11.title: Wine Country
11.plot: At an auction set in wine and horse country, Jesse and David, aka the Leprechaun, spar over bins they hope will have wine in them.

12.title: A Test of Wills
12.plot: Jesse wins a bin that turns out to include a giant pad for stuntmen to land on when they jump out of tall buildings.

13.title: Let It Fly
13.plot: The grand finale is an airport auction with giant hangars filled with cool stuff, including arcade games, lighting equipment, and a vintage El Camino.

imdb.title: Storage Hunters
plot: A group of hunters join in a bidding war for storage lockers that could be a win or a bust.
